Red Hat OpenShift Platform Plus (OCP+)
├── 1. Core Platform: Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform (OCP)
│   ├── 1.1 Kubernetes Core
│   │   ├── Cluster API & Operators
│   │   ├── Kubelet, Kube-API Server, Controller Manager, Scheduler
│   │   ├── etcd (distributed key-value store)
│   │   ├── CRDs (Custom Resource Definitions)
│   │   ├── Admission Controllers
│   │   ├── API aggregation layer
│   │   └── RBAC, Service Accounts, Secrets, ConfigMaps
│   │
│   ├── 1.2 OpenShift Enhancements
│   │   ├── OpenShift API Server
│   │   ├── OpenShift Controller Manager
│   │   ├── OpenShift SDN / CNI integrations (OVN-Kubernetes, Multus, Cilium)
│   │   ├── OpenShift OAuth server
│   │   ├── Cluster Version Operator (CVO)
│   │   ├── Machine Config Operator (MCO)
│   │   ├── Cluster Autoscaler
│   │   ├── Node tuning and performance profiles
│   │   └── Pod Security Admission (PSA)
│   │
│   ├── 1.3 Developer & Build Tools
│   │   ├── Source-to-Image (S2I)
│   │   ├── OpenShift Builds (BuildConfig, Build Pods)
│   │   ├── ImageStreams
│   │   ├── Internal container registry
│   │   ├── OpenShift Pipelines (Tekton)
│   │   ├── OpenShift GitOps (ArgoCD)
│   │   ├── Developer Console (Web UI)
│   │   ├── CodeReady Workspaces (Eclipse Che)
│   │   ├── OpenShift Dev Spaces
│   │   ├── Helm Chart integration
│   │   ├── OperatorHub & Operator Lifecycle Manager (OLM)
│   │   ├── CLI Tools:
│   │   │   ├── oc
│   │   │   ├── odo
│   │   │   ├── kubectl
│   │   │   └── helm
│   │   └── Dev Sandbox & QuickStart templates
│   │
│   ├── 1.4 Networking
│   │   ├── Ingress Controller (HAProxy-based)
│   │   ├── OpenShift Routes (Layer 7 routing)
│   │   ├── LoadBalancer / NodePort / ClusterIP services
│   │   ├── Egress IP and Egress Firewall
│   │   ├── Multus (multiple CNI networks)
│   │   ├── OVN-Kubernetes SDN (default)
│   │   ├── MetalLB (bare metal load balancing)
│   │   ├── DNS Operator
│   │   ├── NetworkPolicy and EgressControl
│   │   ├── Service Mesh integration (Istio)
│   │   └── API Gateway (via 3scale or Istio)
│   │
│   ├── 1.5 Storage
│   │   ├── CSI Drivers (block, file, object)
│   │   ├── OpenShift Data Foundation (ODF) integration
│   │   ├── Persistent Volumes (PV/PVC)
│   │   ├── Dynamic provisioning (RBD, CephFS)
│   │   ├── VolumeSnapshots
│   │   ├── Object storage gateway (RGW)
│   │   └── Ephemeral storage and secrets encryption
│   │
│   ├── 1.6 Security
│   │   ├── OpenShift OAuth / RBAC / SCC
│   │   ├── PodSecurityPolicies (deprecated → PSA)
│   │   ├── Security Context Constraints (SCC)
│   │   ├── Image signing and verification
│   │   ├── Encryption at rest (etcd / PV)
│   │   ├── Audit logging
│   │   ├── OAuth integration (LDAP, SSO, GitHub, OIDC)
│   │   ├── Cluster-wide secret encryption (KMS)
│   │   ├── Network Policies
│   │   └── Compliance Operator (CIS/STIG scans)
│   │
│   ├── 1.7 Monitoring & Logging
│   │   ├── Prometheus Operator
│   │   ├── Alertmanager
│   │   ├── Grafana dashboards
│   │   ├── Cluster Monitoring Stack
│   │   ├── OpenShift Logging Operator
│   │   ├── LokiStack (for logging)
│   │   ├── Elasticsearch (legacy)
│   │   ├── Fluentd / Vector (log collection)
│   │   └── Telemetry and Insights integration
│   │
│   ├── 1.8 Installer & Lifecycle
│   │   ├── IPI (Installer Provisioned Infrastructure)
│   │   ├── UPI (User Provisioned Infrastructure)
│   │   ├── Assisted Installer / Agent-based install
│   │   ├── Cluster Autoscaler
│   │   ├── CVO (Cluster Version Operator)
│   │   ├── Backup and Restore (velero, OADP)
│   │   └── Day-2 Ops (scaling, upgrade, node tuning)
│   │
│   └── 1.9 Integrations
│       ├── Red Hat Enterprise Linux CoreOS (RHCOS)
│       ├── OpenShift Service Mesh
│       ├── OpenShift Serverless (Knative)
│       ├── OpenShift Virtualization (KubeVirt)
│       └── GitOps and Pipelines CI/CD integration
│
│
├── 2. Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management (ACM)
│   ├── 2.1 Multi-cluster Management
│   │   ├── Cluster import, creation, and lifecycle
│   │   ├── Policy-based governance
│   │   ├── Centralized upgrades and health monitoring
│   │   ├── ManagedClusters and Hub/Spoke model
│   │   └── Cluster deployment to AWS, Azure, GCP, vSphere, bare metal
│   │
│   ├── 2.2 Governance, Risk & Compliance (GRC)
│   │   ├── Policy framework (OPA/Gatekeeper)
│   │   ├── Config policy templates (YAML)
│   │   ├── Security posture checks (CIS, NIST)
│   │   ├── Remediation workflows
│   │   └── Integration with ACS policies
│   │
│   ├── 2.3 Application Lifecycle
│   │   ├── ArgoCD-based GitOps management
│   │   ├── Multi-cluster application placement
│   │   ├── AppSets and PlacementRules
│   │   ├── Sync policies
│   │   └── Health and drift detection
│   │
│   ├── 2.4 Observability
│   │   ├── Centralized metrics and logging aggregation
│   │   ├── Cluster health and status dashboards
│   │   ├── Search API across all clusters
│   │   └── Custom labels and inventory
│   │
│   └── 2.5 Integrations
│       ├── OpenShift GitOps (ArgoCD)
│       ├── ACS (policy enforcement)
│       ├── Quay (registry management)
│       ├── RH Insights & Satellite
│       └── Integration with SSO / LDAP
│
│
├── 3. Red Hat Advanced Cluster Security (ACS)
│   ├── 3.1 Core Components
│   │   ├── Central (management console)
│   │   ├── Sensor (per cluster)
│   │   ├── Collector (per node)
│   │   ├── Admission controller webhook
│   │   ├── Postgres (metadata DB)
│   │   └── RHACS Operator
│   │
│   ├── 3.2 Security Capabilities
│   │   ├── Image scanning (via Clair / Quay)
│   │   ├── Runtime behavior detection
│   │   ├── Policy enforcement (build, deploy, runtime)
│   │   ├── Network graph and flow visualization
│   │   ├── Risk prioritization and CVSS scoring
│   │   ├── Kubernetes audit log correlation
│   │   ├── Admission control integration
│   │   └── Compliance framework (CIS, PCI-DSS, NIST)
│   │
│   ├── 3.3 Integrations
│   │   ├── Quay registry
│   │   ├── OpenShift OAuth / SSO
│   │   ├── CI/CD systems (Jenkins, Tekton)
│   │   ├── GitOps / ArgoCD
│   │   ├── ACM policies
│   │   └── External SIEM tools (Splunk, QRadar)
│   │
│   └── 3.4 Observability
│       ├── Central dashboard
│       ├── Risk reports
│       ├── Compliance dashboards
│       └── Alert integrations (Slack, PagerDuty, Webhook)
│
│
├── 4. Red Hat Quay (Enterprise Image Registry)
│   ├── 4.1 Quay Core
│   │   ├── Web UI & API
│   │   ├── Redis cache
│   │   ├── PostgreSQL backend
│   │   ├── Object storage (S3, Ceph, Azure)
│   │   ├── Clair (vulnerability scanning)
│   │   ├── Quay Builder
│   │   └── Quay Operator (deployment automation)
│   │
│   ├── 4.2 Features
│   │   ├── Authentication (LDAP, OIDC, SSO)
│   │   ├── RBAC and Team permissions
│   │   ├── Image signing (Cosign)
│   │   ├── CVE scanning and blocking
│   │   ├── Mirroring and geo-replication
│   │   ├── Tag immutability and retention policies
│   │   └── Integration with ACS for policy enforcement
│
│
├── 5. Red Hat OpenShift Data Foundation (ODF)
│   ├── 5.1 Storage Backends
│   │   ├── Ceph (RBD, CephFS, RGW)
│   │   ├── NooBaa (object data gateway)
│   │   └── Multi-cloud object gateway
│   │
│   ├── 5.2 Capabilities
│   │   ├── Block / File / Object unified storage
│   │   ├── Dynamic provisioning via CSI
│   │   ├── Data replication & disaster recovery
│   │   ├── Snapshots and clones
│   │   ├── Encryption and key management
│   │   ├── Data resilience and self-healing
│   │   └── Integration with Quay and ACS
│   │
│   └── 5.3 Management
│       ├── ODF Operator
│       ├── Dashboard (via OpenShift Console)
│       └── Performance and capacity metrics
│
│
├── 6. Optional Integrated Components
│   ├── OpenShift Service Mesh (Istio-based)
│   │   ├── Envoy sidecar proxy
│   │   ├── Kiali dashboard
│   │   ├── Jaeger tracing
│   │   ├── Prometheus metrics
│   │   └── Policy and telemetry
│   │
│   ├── OpenShift Serverless (Knative)
│   │   ├── Eventing and autoscaling
│   │   ├── Functions-as-a-Service (FaaS)
│   │   └── Integration with Pipelines and GitOps
│   │
│   ├── OpenShift Virtualization (KubeVirt)
│   │   ├── Run VMs on Kubernetes
│   │   ├── VM templates and hotplug disks
│   │   └── Migration from VMware
│   │
│   ├── OpenShift GitOps (ArgoCD)
│   │   ├── GitOps Application CRD
│   │   ├── Sync and health checks
│   │   ├── Multi-environment pipeline (Dev/UAT/Prod)
│   │   └── Integration with ACM and Pipelines
│   │
│   └── OpenShift Pipelines (Tekton)
│       ├── Custom Tasks and TaskRuns
│       ├── PipelineRuns and Triggers
│       ├── Secrets and Workspaces
│       ├── Build and deploy automation
│       └── Integration with Quay, GitOps, and ACS
│
│
└── 7. Platform Plus Value Additions
    ├── Unified Hybrid Cloud Platform
    │   ├── Multi-cluster management (ACM)
    │   ├── Multi-layer security (ACS)
    │   ├── Enterprise image registry (Quay)
    │   ├── Persistent data layer (ODF)
    │   └── Automation (GitOps, Pipelines)
    │
    ├── Advanced Security
    │   ├── Policy-driven governance (ACM+ACS)
    │   ├── Image supply chain security (Quay+ACS)
    │   ├── Compliance enforcement
    │   ├── Cluster risk visibility
    │   └── Runtime anomaly detection
    │
    ├── Unified Observability
    │   ├── Central monitoring dashboards
    │   ├── Federated logging (via Loki)
    │   ├── Cross-cluster search (ACM)
    │   └── Global health and performance view
    │
    └── Enterprise Lifecycle
        ├── Multi-cluster upgrades
        ├── Policy-based deployment pipelines
        ├── Compliance at scale
        └── Backup & DR with ODF + ACM integration
